{"title_page": "List of Parliamentary constituencies in Dyfed", "text_new": "Five '''constituencies''' cover '''Dyfed''', also used for elections to the [[National Assembly for Wales]]. The current boundaries have been effective since the [[2007 National Assembly for Wales election|2007 Welsh Assembly election]] and the [[2010 United Kingdom general election]].<ref>[http://www.opsi.gov.uk/si/si2006/20061041.htm ''The Parliamentary Constituencies and Assembly Electoral Regions (Wales) Order 2006'', OPSI website]</ref>{{refn|group=n|They are all [[County constituencies|county constituencies (CCs)]] of the [[House of Commons (UK)|House of Commons]] of the [[Parliament of the United Kingdom]] ([[Palace of Westminster|Westminster]])}}\n\n[[Dyfed]] is one of the eight [[Preserved counties of Wales|preserved counties]] of [[Wales]], consisting of the [[Principal areas of Wales|principal areas]] of [[Pembrokeshire]], [[Carmarthenshire]] and [[Ceredigion]].\nThese principal areas are also known as counties.\n\nFor Welsh Assembly elections, constituencies are grouped into [[Additional member system|additional member]] [[National Assembly for Wales constituencies and regions|electoral regions]].\n\n== Westminster boundaries ==\n\n=== From 2010 ===\n\n{| border=1 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\"\n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Boundaries\n|-\n| 1. [[Carmarthen East and Dinefwr (UK Parliament constituency)|Carmarthen East and Dinefwr CC (Westminster)]] ||rowspan=5| [[Image:DyfedParliamentaryConstituencies2007.svg|left|200px|Parliamentary constituencies in Dyfed 2010]]\n|-\n| 2. [[Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire CC (Westminster)]]\n|-\n| 3. [[Ceredigion (UK Parliament constituency)|Ceredigion CC (Westminster)]]\n|-\n| 4. [[Llanelli (UK Parliament constituency)|Llanelli CC (Westminster)]]\n|-\n| 5. [[Preseli Pembrokeshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Preseli Pembrokeshire CC (Westminster)]]\n|}\n\n{{legend2|{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] \u2020|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] \u2021|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Plaid Cymru/meta/color}}|[[Plaid Cymru]] \u20aa|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!rowspan=1|Constituency\n!rowspan=1|Electorate\n!rowspan=1|Majority\n!colspan=2 class=unsortable|[[Member of Parliament]]\n!colspan=2 class=unsortable|Nearest opposition\n<!--!rowspan=1 class=unsortable|Electoral wards<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.opsi.gov.uk/si/si2007/uksi_20071681_en_4|title=The Parliamentary Constituencies (Wales) Order 2007|publisher=Crown copyright|work=[[Office of Public Sector Information]]|accessdate=7 November 2009|date=13 June 2007}}</ref><ref>[[Boundary Commissions (United Kingdom)|Boundary Commission for Wales]] pp. 1004\u20131007</ref> -->\n!rowspan=1 class=unsortable|Map reference above\n|-\n|[[Carmarthen East and Dinefwr (UK Parliament constituency)|Carmarthen East and Dinefwr CC (Westminster)]]\n|57,407\n|1,809\n|bgcolor={{Plaid Cymru/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Jonathan Edwards (Welsh politician)|Jonathan Edwards]] \u20aa\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|Havard Hughes \u2020\n|1\n|-\n|[[Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire CC (Westminster)]]\n|58,629\n|7,745\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Simon Hart]] \u2020\n|bgcolor={{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|Marc Tierney \u2021\n|2\n|-\n|[[Ceredigion (UK Parliament constituency)|Ceredigion CC (Westminster)]]\n|56,250\n|6,329\n|bgcolor={{Plaid Cymru/meta/color}}|&nbsp;                                   \n|[[Ben Lake]] \u20aa\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|Amanda Jenner \u2020\n|3\n|-\n|[[Llanelli (UK Parliament constituency)|Llanelli CC (Westminster)]]\n|60,513\n|4,670\n|bgcolor={{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Nia Griffith]] \u2021\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|Tamara Reay \u2020\n|4\n|-\n|[[Preseli Pembrokeshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Preseli Pembrokeshire CC (Westminster)]]\n|59,586\n|5,062\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Stephen Crabb]] \u2020\n|bgcolor={{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|Philippa Thompson \u2021\n|5\n|}\n\n=== 1997 to 2010 ===\n\n{| border=1 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\"\n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Boundaries\n|-\n| 1. [[Carmarthen East and Dinefwr (UK Parliament constituency)|Carmarthen East and Dinefwr CC (Westminster)]] ||rowspan=5| [[Image:DyfedParliamentaryConstituenciesPre2007.png|left|Parliamentary constituencies in Dyfed pre-2010]]\n|-\n| 2. [[Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire CC (Westminster)]]\n|-\n| 3. [[Ceredigion (UK Parliament constituency)|Ceredigion CC (Westminster)]]\n|-\n| 4. [[Llanelli (UK Parliament constituency)|Llanelli CC (Westminster)]]\n|-\n| 5. [[Preseli Pembrokeshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Preseli Pembrokeshire CC (Westminster)]]\n|}\n\n==Changes proposed in 2018==\n\nAs part of the [[Sixth Periodic Review of Westminster constituencies]] the Boundary Commission for Wales proposed changes to almost all the existing Welsh Westminster constituencies, giving their proposals official names in either English or Wales and offering an alternative in the other language.<ref>[http://bcomm-wales.gov.uk/?skip=1&lang=en Final Recommendations 2018] Boundary Commission for Wales]</ref>\n\n*[[Llanelli (UK Parliament constituency)|Llanelli]]\n*[[Caerfyrddin (UK Parliament constituency)|Caerfyrddin]]\n*[[Mid and South Pembrokeshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Mid and South Pembrokeshire]]\n*[[Ceredigion a Gogledd Sir Benfro (UK Parliament constituency)|Ceredigion a Gogledd Sir Benfro]]\n\n== Assembly boundaries ==\n\n=== From 2007 ===\n\n{| border=1 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\"\n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Assembly region !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency boundaries\n|-\n| 1. [[Carmarthen East and Dinefwr (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Carmarthen East and Dinefwr CC (Assembly)]] ||rowspan=5| [[Mid and West Wales (National Assembly for Wales electoral region)|Mid and West Wales]] || rowspan=5| [[Image:DyfedParliamentaryConstituencies2007.svg|left|200px|Assembly constituencies in Dyfed 2007]]\n|-\n| 2. [[Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire CC (Assembly)]]\n|-\n| 3. [[Ceredigion (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Ceredigion CC (Assembly)]]\n|-\n| 4. [[Llanelli (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Llanelli CC (Assembly)]]\n|-\n| 5. [[Preseli Pembrokeshire (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Preseli Pembrokeshire CC (Assembly)]]\n|}\n\nThe Mid and West Wales region also includes two [[List of Parliamentary constituencies in Powys|Powys constituencies]] and one [[List of Parliamentary constituencies in Gwynedd|Gwynedd constituency]].\n\n=== 1999 to 2007 ===\n\n{| border=1 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\"\n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Assembly region !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency boundaries\n|-\n| 1. [[Carmarthen East and Dinefwr (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Carmarthen East and Dinefwr CC (Assembly)]] ||rowspan=5| [[Mid and West Wales (National Assembly for Wales electoral region)|Mid and West Wales]] || rowspan=5| [[Image:DyfedParliamentaryConstituenciesPre2007.png|left|Assembly constituencies in Dyfed pre-2007]]\n|-\n| 2. [[Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire CC (Assembly)]]\n|-\n| 3. [[Ceredigion (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Ceredigion CC (Assembly)]]\n|-\n| 4. [[Llanelli (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Llanelli CC (Assembly)]]\n|-\n| 5. [[Preseli Pembrokeshire (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Preseli Pembrokeshire CC (Assembly)]]\n|}\n\n== Historical representation by party ==\nA cell marked \u2192 (with a different colour background to the preceding cell) indicates that the previous MP continued to sit under a new party name.\n\n===1832 to 1885===\n{{legend2|{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Liberal Party (UK)|Liberal]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Peelite/meta/color}}|[[Peelite]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Radicals (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Radicals (UK)|Radical]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Whigs (British political party)/meta/color}}|[[Whigs (British political party)|Whig]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Constituency\n!1832\n!1835\n!1837\n!''38''\n!1841\n!''42''\n!''46''\n!1847\n!''49''\n!''52''\n!1852\n!''54''\n!''55''\n!1857\n!''57''\n!1859\n!''61''\n!''64''\n!1865\n!''66''\n!1868\n!1874\n!''76''\n!''78''\n!1880\n!''82''\n|-\n|[[Cardigan Boroughs (UK Parliament constituency)|Cardigan Boroughs]]\n| colspan=\"8\" bgcolor=\"{{Whigs (British political party)/meta/color}}\" |[[Pryse Pryse|P. Pryse]]\n| colspan=\"4\" bgcolor=\"{{Whigs (British political party)/meta/color}}\" |[[Pryse Loveden|Loveden]]\n|bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|[[John Lloyd Davies|J. Davies]]\n| colspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"{{Radicals (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Edward Pryse|E. Pryse]]\n| colspan=\"5\" bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Edward Pryse|\u2192]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Sir Thomas Lloyd, 1st Baronet|T. Lloyd]]\n| colspan=\"5\" bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[David Davies (industrialist)|D. Davies]]\n|-\n|[[Cardiganshire (UK Parliament constituency)