t and South Pembrokeshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire CC (Westminster)]]\n|58,629\n|7,745\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Simon Hart]] \u2020\n|bgcolor={{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|Marc Tierney \u2021\n|2\n|-\n|[[Ceredigion (UK Parliament constituency)|Ceredigion CC (Westminster)]]\n|56,250\n|6,329\n|bgcolor={{Plaid Cymru/meta/color}}|&nbsp;                                   \n|[[Ben Lake]] \u20aa\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|Amanda Jenner \u2020\n|3\n|-\n|[[Llanelli (UK Parliament constituency)|Llanelli CC (Westminster)]]\n|60,513\n|4,670\n|bgcolor={{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Nia Griffith]] \u2021\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|Tamara Reay \u2020\n|4\n|-\n|[[Preseli Pembrokeshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Preseli Pembrokeshire CC (Westminster)]]\n|59,586\n|5,062\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Stephen Crabb]] \u2020\n|bgcolor={{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|Philippa Thompson \u2021\n|5\n|}\n\n=== 1997 to 2010 ===\n\n{| border=1 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\"\n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Boundaries\n|-\n| 1. [[Carmarthen East and Dinefwr (UK Parliament constituency)|Carmarthen East and Dinefwr CC (Westminster)]] ||rowspan=5| [[Image:DyfedParliamentaryConstituenciesPre2007.png|left|Parliamentary constituencies in Dyfed pre-2010]]\n|-\n| 2. [[Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire CC (Westminster)]]\n|-\n| 3. [[Ceredigion (UK Parliament constituency)|Ceredigion CC (Westminster)]]\n|-\n| 4. [[Llanelli (UK Parliament constituency)|Llanelli CC (Westminster)]]\n|-\n| 5. [[Preseli Pembrokeshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Preseli Pembrokeshire CC (Westminster)]]\n|}\n\n==Changes proposed for 2022==\n\nAs part of the [[Sixth Periodic Review of Westminster constituencies]] the Boundary Commission for Wales proposed changes to almost all the existing Welsh Westminster constituencies, giving their proposals official names in either English or Wales and offering an alternative in the other language.<ref>[http://bcomm-wales.gov.uk/?skip=1&lang=en Final Recommendations 2018] Boundary Commission for Wales]</ref>\n\n*[[Llanelli (UK Parliament constituency)|Llanelli]]\n*[[Caerfyrddin (UK Parliament constituency)|Caerfyrddin]]\n*[[Mid and South Pembrokeshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Mid and South Pembrokeshire]]\n*[[Ceredigion a Gogledd Sir Benfro (UK Parliament constituency)|Ceredigion a Gogledd Sir Benfro]]\n\n== Assembly boundaries ==\n\n=== From 2007 ===\n\n{| border=1 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\"\n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Assembly region !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency boundaries\n|-\n| 1. [[Carmarthen East and Dinefwr (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Carmarthen East and Dinefwr CC (Assembly)]] ||rowspan=5| [[Mid and West Wales (National Assembly for Wales electoral region)|Mid and West Wales]] || rowspan=5| [[Image:DyfedParliamentaryConstituencies2007.svg|left|200px|Assembly constituencies in Dyfed 2007]]\n|-\n| 2. [[Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire CC (Assembly)]]\n|-\n| 3. [[Ceredigion (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Ceredigion CC (Assembly)]]\n|-\n| 4. [[Llanelli (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Llanelli CC (Assembly)]]\n|-\n| 5. [[Preseli Pembrokeshire (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Preseli Pembrokeshire CC (Assembly)]]\n|}\n\nThe Mid and West Wales region also includes two [[List of Parliamentary constituencies in Powys|Powys constituencies]] and one [[List of Parliamentary constituencies in Gwynedd|Gwynedd constituency]].\n\n=== 1999 to 2007 ===\n\n{| border=1 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\"\n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency !! bgcolor=