{"title_page": "BPMD", "text_new": "{{distinguish|EPMD}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                = BPMD\n| image               = Overkill - Jalometalli 2008 - 02.JPG\n| caption             = \n| image_size          = \n| landscape           = \n| background          = group_or_band\n| alias               = \n| origin              = \n| genre               = \n| years_active        = {{Start date|2019}}\u2013present\n| label               = [[Napalm Records]]\n| associated_acts     = [[Metal Allegiance]]\n| website             = \n| current_members     = [[Bobby Ellsworth|Bobby \"Blitz\" Ellsworth]]<br>[[Phil Demmel]]<br>Mark Menghi<br>[[Mike Portnoy]]\n| past_members        = \n}}\n'''BPMD''' is an American [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]] [[supergroup (music)|supergroup]]. Formed in 2019, the band consists of [[Overkill (band)|Overkill]] vocalist [[Bobby Ellsworth|Bobby \"Blitz\" Ellsworth]], [[Vio-lence]] and former [[Machine Head (band)|Machine Head]] guitarist [[Phil Demmel]], and two members of [[Metal Allegiance]]\u2013bassist Mark Menghi and drummer [[Mike Portnoy]].\n\n==History==\nBPMD was conceived in the summer of 2019 when Ellsworth, Demmel, Menghi and Portnoy teamed up to record an album featuring covers of 1970s songs, titled ''American Made''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/current-former-members-of-machine-head-dream-theater-overkill-unite-in-new-project/|title=Current/Former Members Of MACHINE HEAD, DREAM THEATER, OVERKILL Unite In New Project|publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=April 15, 2020|date=August 7, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/overkills-blitz-details-made-in-america-project-with-mike-portnoy-and-phil-demmel/|title=OVERKILL's BLITZ Details 'Made In America' Project With MIKE PORTNOY And PHIL DEMMEL|publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=April 15, 2020|date=September 27, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://blabbermouth.net/news/phil-demmel-on-his-collaboration-with-mike-portnoy-and-bobby-blitz-ellsworth-it-was-pretty-rad-playing-with-those-dudes/|title=PHIL DEMMEL On His Collaboration With MIKE PORTNOY And BOBBY 'BLITZ' ELLSWORTH: 'It Was Pretty Rad Playing With Those Dudes'|publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=April 15, 2020|date=October 21, 2019}}</ref> In a January 2020 interview on The Blairing Out with Eric Blair Show, Demmel revealed that the project would be called BPMD, in reference to three of the members' last names as well as Ellsworth's nickname Blitz. About the project, he said: \"It's all cover tunes from American bands of the '70s. It's called ''American Made'', [and it's got songs from] [[ZZ Top]], [[Lynyrd Skynyrd]], [[James Gang]], [[Aerosmith]], [[Grand Funk Railroad]] \u2014 all these cover tunes that we modernized them and not really thrashed them up, but we made kind of metal versions of them. And we think we found maybe a label home, and we're looking to put the record out here probably at the end of the first quarter, maybe beginning of second quarter. It's all up in the air right now.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/bobby-blitz-ellsworth-mike-portnoy-phil-demmel-and-mark-menghi-join-forces-in-bpmd-american-made-album-due-soon/|title=BOBBY 'BLITZ' ELLSWORTH, MIKE PORTNOY, PHIL DEMMEL And MARK MENGHI Join Forces In BPMD: 'American Made' Album Due Soon|publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=April 15, 2020|date=January 31, 2020}}</ref>\n\n''American Made'' is due for release on June 12, 2020 through [[Napalm Records]], and will include ten song covers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/bpmd-feat-bobby-blitz-ellsworth-mike-portnoy-phil-demmel-and-mark-menghi-debut-album-to-be-released-via-napalm/|title=BPMD Feat. BOBBY 'BLITZ' ELLSWORTH, MIKE PORTNOY, PHIL DEMMEL And MARK MENGHI: Debut Album To Be Released Via NAPALM|publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=April 15, 2020|date=March 25, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/bpmd-feat-bobby-blitz-ellsworth-mike-portnoy-phil-demmel-and-mark-menghi-american-made-album-details-revealed/|title=BPMD Feat. BOBBY 'BLITZ' ELLSWORTH, MIKE PORTNOY, PHIL DEMMEL And MARK MENGHI: 'American Made' Album Details Revealed|publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=April 15, 2020|date=April 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n* ''American Made'' (2020)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{US-metal-band-stub}}\n\n[[Category:Musical quartets]]\n[[Category:Supergroups (music)]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2019]]\n[[Category:Heavy metal supergroups]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|EPMD}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                = BPMD\n| image               = Overkill - Jalometalli 2008 - 02.JPG\n| caption             = \n| image_size          = \n| landscape           = \n| background          = group_or_band\n| alias               = \n| origin              = \n| genre               = \n| years_active        = {{Start date|2019}}\u2013present\n| label               = [[Napalm Records]]\n| associated_acts     = [[Overkill (band)|Overkill]], [[Vio-lence]], [[Machine Head (band)|Machine Head]], [[Metal Allegiance]], [[Dream Theater]], [[The Winery Dogs]], [[Sons of Apollo]]\n| website             = \n| current_members     = [[Bobby Ellsworth|Bobby \"Blitz\" Ellsworth]]<br>[[Phil Demmel]]<br>Mark Menghi<br>[[Mike Portnoy]]\n| past_members        = \n}}\n'''BPMD''' is an American [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]] [[supergroup (music)|supergroup]]. Formed in 2019, the band consists of [[Overkill (band)|Overkill]] vocalist [[Bobby Ellsworth|Bobby \"Blitz\" Ellsworth]], [[Vio-lence]] and former [[Machine Head (band)|Machine Head]] guitarist [[Phil Demmel]], and two members of [[Metal Allegiance]]\u2013bassist Mark Menghi and drummer [[Mike Portnoy]].\n\n==History==\nBPMD was conceived in the summer of 2019 when Ellsworth, Demmel, Menghi and Portnoy teamed up to record an album featuring covers of 1970s songs, titled ''American Made''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/current-former-members-of-machine-head-dream-theater-overkill-unite-in-new-project/|title=Current/Former Members Of MACHINE HEAD, DREAM THEATER, OVERKILL Unite In New Project|publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=April 15, 2020|date=August 7, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/overkills-blitz-details-made-in-america-project-with-mike-portnoy-and-phil-demmel/|title=OVERKILL's BLITZ Details 'Made In America' Project With MIKE PORTNOY And PHIL DEMMEL|publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=April 15, 2020|date=September 27, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://blabbermouth.net/news/phil-demmel-on-his-collaboration-with-mike-portnoy-and-bobby-blitz-ellsworth-it-was-pretty-rad-playing-with-those-dudes/|title=PHIL DEMMEL On His Collaboration With MIKE PORTNOY And BOBBY 'BLITZ' ELLSWORTH: 'It Was Pretty Rad Playing With Those Dudes'|publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=April 15, 2020|date=October 21, 2019}}</ref> In a January 2020 interview on The Blairing Out with Eric Blair Show, Demmel revealed that the project would be called BPMD, in reference to three of the members' last names as well as Ellsworth's nickname Blitz. About the project, he said: \"It's all cover tunes from American bands of the '70s. It's called ''American Made'', [and it's got songs from] [[ZZ Top]], [[Lynyrd Skynyrd]], [[James Gang]], [[Aerosmith]], [[Grand Funk Railroad]] \u2014 all these cover tunes that we modernized them and not really thrashed them up, but we made kind of metal versions of them. And we think we found maybe a label home, and we're looking to put the record out here probably at the end of the first quarter, maybe beginning of second quarter. It's all up in the air right now.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/bobby-blitz-ellsworth-mike-portnoy-phil-demmel-and-mark-menghi-join-forces-in-bpmd-american-made-album-due-soon/|title=BOBBY 'BLITZ' ELLSWORTH, MIKE PORTNOY, PHIL DEMMEL And MARK MENGHI Join Forces In BPMD: 'American Made' Album Due Soon|publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=April 15, 2020|date=January 31, 2020}}</ref>\n\n''American Made'' is due for release on June 12, 2020 through [[Napalm Records]], and will include ten song covers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/bpmd-feat-bobby-blitz-ellsworth-mike-portnoy-phil-demmel-and-mark-menghi-debut-album-to-be-released-via-napalm/|title=BPMD Feat. BOBBY 'BLITZ' ELLSWORTH, MIKE PORTNOY, PHIL DEMMEL And MARK MENGHI: Debut Album To Be Released Via NAPALM|publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=April 15, 2020|date=March 25, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/bpmd-feat-bobby-blitz-ellsworth-mike-portnoy-phil-demmel-and-mark-menghi-american-made-album-details-revealed/|title=BPMD Feat. BOBBY 'BLITZ' ELLSWORTH, MIKE PORTNOY, PHIL DEMMEL And MARK MENGHI: 'American Made' Album Details Revealed|publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=April 15, 2020|date=April 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n* ''American Made'' (2020)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{US-metal-band-stub}}\n\n[[Category:Musical quartets]]\n[[Category:Supergroups (music)]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2019]]\n[[Category:Heavy metal supergroups]]\n", "name_user": "Victor Lopes", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Template:Infobox musical artist#associated_acts", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BPMD"}
