\u201309\n| ''[[The Replacements (TV series)|The Replacements]]''\n| The voice of C.A.R.\n|-\n| 2008\u201310\n| ''[[Ben 10: Alien Force]]''\n| Professor Paradox (voice)\n| Recurring role\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Batman: The Brave and the Bold]]''\n| [[Merlin (DC Comics)|Merlin Ambrosius]]\n| Episode: \"Day of the Dark Knight!\" (S 1:Ep 5)\n|-\n| 2010\u201312\n| ''[[Ben 10: Ultimate Alien]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Professor Paradox (voice)\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Recurring role\n|-\n| 2013\u201314\n| ''[[Ben 10: Omniverse]]''\n|-\n| 2014, 2016\n| ''[[NCIS: New Orleans]]''\n| Dr. Donald \"Ducky\" Mallard\n| Episodes: \"Musician Heal Thyself\" (S 1:Ep 1), \"Sister City, Part II\" (S 2:Ep 12)\n|- \n| 2019\n| ''D-Day at Pointe-du-Hoc''\n| Narrator (PBS documentary)\n|\n|}\n\n===Video games===\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''[[Wing Commander (franchise)#Privateer 2: The Darkening|Privateer 2: The Darkening]]''\n| Captain of the ''Canera''\n| {{Plainlist|\n* Appears in the opening full-motion video cinematic\n}}\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Ben 10 Alien Force: Vilgax Attacks|Ben 10: Alien Force - Vilgax Attacks]]''\n| Professor Paradox\n| \n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Cartoon Network Universe: FusionFall|FusionFall]]''\n| Paradox\n| \n|-\n| 2011\n| ''NCIS Video Game''\n| Dr. Donald \"Ducky\" Mallard\n| {{Plainlist|\n* Voices his character from ''NCIS''\n* Narrates the game\n}}\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Diablo III: Reaper of Souls]]''\n| The Grand Maester / King Rakkis\n| His voice only appears in the [[Diablo III]] expansion [[Downloadable content|DLC]], Reaper of Souls.\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Biography|Scotland|California|New York City|Theatre|Film|Television|Music}}\n{{commons category}}\n* [http://www.davidmccallumfansonline.com David McCallum Fans Online]\n* [http://www.manfromuncle.org Fans from U.N.C.L.E.]\n* {{IMDb name|0564724}}\n* {{IBDB name}}\n* {{iobdb name|1363}}\n* {{TV Guide person |david-mccallum/146571}}\n\n{{Au