uary 29, 2020}}</ref>\n\n<!-- NEED SOURCE\n<ref name=\"RPS\">{{cite web |url=https://intothespine.com/2019/01/10/to-be-gay-in-mass-effect-rebellion/|title=The Sunday Papers|author=Matt Cox|date=January 20, 2019|work=[[Rock, Paper, Shotgun]]|accessdate=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Mic\">{{cite web |url=https://www.mic.com/articles/172092/mass-effect-andromeda-romance-gay-players-feel-neglected-this-chart-proves-it-s-true|title=Mass Effect Andromeda' Romance: Gay players feel neglected \u2014 this chart proves it's true|author=Tim Mulkerin|date=March 25, 2017|work=Mic|accessdate=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\nhttps://www.gamasutra.com/view/feature/134828/ethical_dilemmas_and_dominant_.php?page=2\n-->\n}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Alenko, Kaidan}}\n\n{{Mass Effect}}\n[[Category:Fictional bisexual males]]\n[[Category:Fictional bodyguards]]\n[[Category:Fictional Canadian people]]\n[[Category:Fictional military personnel in video games]]\n[[Category:Fictional secret agents and spies]]\n[[Category:Fictional special forces personnel]]\n[[Category:Fictional murdered people in video games]]\n[[Category:Fictional telekinetics]]\n[[Category:Fictional war veterans]]\n[[Category:LGBT characters in video games]]\n[[Category:Male characters in video games]]\n[[Category:Mass Effect characters]]\n[[Category:Video game characters introduced in 2007]]\n[[Category:Video game sidekicks]]\n[[Category:Fictional characters from British Columbia]]\n", "name_user": "Haleth", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eSame-Sex Romance Option", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kaidan_Alenko"}
{"title_page": "List of Parliamentary constituencies in Clwyd", "text_new": "Seven '''constituencies''' cover '''Clwyd'''. They are [[County constituencies|county constituencies (CCs)]] (for type of returning officer and election expenses) of the [[House of Commons (UK)|House of Commons]] of the [[Parliament of the United Kingdom|UK Parliament]] ([[Palace of Westminster|Westminster]]), and are used also for elections to the [[National Assembly for Wales]]. The current boundaries have been effective since the [[2007 National Assembly for Wales election]] and the [[2010 United Kingdom general election]].<ref>[http://www.opsi.gov.uk/si/si2006/20061041.htm ''The Parliamentary Constituencies and Assembly Electoral Regions (Wales) Order 2006'', OPSI website]</ref>\n\n[[Clwyd]] is one of the eight [[Preserved counties of Wales|preserved counties]] of [[Wales]]. As currently defined, the preserved county consists of the [[Principal areas of Wales|principal areas]] of [[Conwy (county borough)|Conwy]], [[Denbighshire]], [[Flintshire]] and [[Wrexham (county borough)|Wrexham]].\n\nFor Welsh Assembly elections, constituencies are grouped into [[Additional member system|additional member]] [[National Assembly for Wales constituencies and regions|electoral regions]], and changes to constituency boundaries mean, also, changes to regional boundaries.\n\n== Westminster boundaries ==\n\n=== From 2010 ===\n\n{| border=1 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" \n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Boundaries\n|-\n| 1. [[Aberconwy (UK Parliament constituency)|Aberconwy CC]] || rowspan=7| [[Image:ClwydParliamentaryConstituencies2007.svg|left|200px|Parliamentary constituencies in Clwyd 2010]]\n|-\n| 2. [[Alyn and Deeside (UK Parliament constituency)|Alyn and Deeside CC]]\n|-\n| 3. [[Clwyd South (UK Parliament constituency)|Clwyd South CC]]\n|-\n| 4. [[Clwyd West (UK Parliament constituency)|Clwyd West CC]]\n|-\n| 5. [[Delyn (UK Parliament constituency)|Delyn CC]]\n|-\n| 6. [[Vale of Clwyd (UK Parliament constituency)|Vale of Clwyd CC]]\n|-\n| 7. [[Wrexham (UK Parliament constituency)|Wrexham CC]]\n|}\n\n{{legend2|{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] \u2020|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] \u2021|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!rowspan=1|Constituency\n!rowspan=1|Electorate\n!rowspan=1|Majority\n!colspan=2 class=unsortable|[[Member of Parliament]]\n!colspan=2 class=unsortable|Nearest opposition\n<!--!rowspan=1 class=unsortable|Electoral wards<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.opsi.gov.uk/si/si2007/uksi_20071681_en_4|title=The Parliamentary Constituencies (Wales) Order 2007|publisher=Crown copyright|work=[[Office of Public Sector Information]]|accessdate=7 November 2009|date=13 June 2007}}</ref><ref>[[Boundary Commissions (United Kingdom)|Boundary Commission for Wales]] pp. 1004\u20131007</ref> -->\n!rowspan=1 class=unsortable|Map reference above\n|-\n|Aberconwy \n|44,699\n|2,034\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Robin Millar]] \u2020\n|bgcolor={{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|Emily Owen \u2021\n|1\n|-\n|Alyn and Deeside \n|62,783\n|213\n|bgcolor={{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Mark Tami]] \u2021\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|Sanjoy Sen \u2020\n|2\n|-\n|Clwyd South\n|53,919\n|1,239\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Simon Baynes]] \u2020\n|bgcolor={{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Susan Jones|Susan Elan Jones]] \u2021\n|3\n|-\n|Clwyd West\n|57,714\n|6,747\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[David Jones (MP for Clwyd West)|David Jones]] \u2020\n|bgcolor={{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|Jo Thomas \u2021\n|4\n|-\n|Delyn\n|54,552\n|865\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Rob Roberts]] \u2020\n|bgcolor={{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[David Hanson (politician)|David Hanson]] \u2021\n|5\n|-\n|Vale of Clwyd\n|56,649\n|1,827\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[James Davies (politician)|James Davies]] \u2020\n|bgcolor={{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Chris Ruane]] \u2021\n|6\n|-\n|Wrexham\n|49,734\n|2,131\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Sarah Atherton]] \u2020\n|bgcolor={{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|Mary Wimbury \u2021\n|7\n|}\n\n=== 1997 to 2010 ===\n\n{| border=1 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" \n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Boundaries\n|-\n| 1. [[Alyn and Deeside (UK Parliament constituency)|Alyn and Deeside CC (Westminster)]] || rowspan=8| [[Image:ClwydParliamentaryConstituenciesPre2007.png|left|Parliamentary constituencies in Clwyd pre-2010]]\n|-\n| 2. [[Clwyd South (UK Parliament constituency)|Clwyd South CC (Westminster)]] (part) \n|-\n| 3. [[Clwyd West (UK Parliament constituency)|Clwyd West CC (Westminster)]]\n|-\n| 4. [[Conwy (UK Parliament constituency)|Conwy CC (Westminster)]] (part)\n|-\n| 5. [[Delyn (UK Parliament constituency)|Delyn CC (Westminster)]]\n|-\n| 6. [[Meirionnydd Nant Conwy (UK Parliament constituency)|Meirionnydd Nant Conwy CC (Westminster)]] (part) \n|-\n| 7. [[Vale of Clwyd (UK Parliament constituency)|Vale of Clwyd CC (Westminster)]] \n|- \n| 8. [[Wrexham (UK Parliament constituency)|Wrexham CC (Westminster)]]\n|}\n\nThe Clwyd South constituency was also partly a [[List of Parliamentary constituencies in Powys|Powys constituency]], and the Conwy and Meirionnydd Nant Conwy constituencies were also partly [[List of Parliamentary constituencies in Gwynedd|Gwynedd constituencies]].\n\n==Changes proposed in 2018==\n\nAs part of the [[Sixth Periodic Review of Westminster constituencies]] the Boundary Commission for Wales proposed changes to almost all the existing Welsh Westminster constituencies, giving their proposals official names in either English or Wales and offering an alternative in the other language.<ref>[http://bcomm-wales.gov.uk/?skip=1&lang=en Final Recommendations 2018] Boundary Commission for Wales]</ref>\n\n*[[Ynys M\u00f4n a Bangor (UK Parliament constituency)|Ynys M\u00f4n a Bangor]]\n*[[Gwynedd (UK Parliament constituency)|Gwynedd]]\n*[[Conwy and Colwyn (UK Parliament constituency)|Conwy and Colwyn]]\n*[[Rhuddlan and Flint (UK Parliament constituency)|Rhuddlan and Flint]]\n*[[Alyn and Deeside (UK Parliament constituency)|Alyn and Deeside]]\n*[[Wrexham (UK Parliament constituency)|Wrexham]]\n*[[De Clwyd a Gogledd Maldwyn (UK Parliament constituency)|De Clwyd a Gogledd Maldwyn]]\n\n== Assembly boundaries ==\n\n=== From 2007 ===\n\n{| border=1 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" \n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Assembly region !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency boundaries\n|-\n| 1. [[Aberconwy (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Aberconwy CC (Assembly)]] || rowspan=7| [[North Wales (National Assembly for Wales electoral region)|North Wales]] || rowspan=7| [[Image:ClwydParliamentaryConstituencies2007.svg|left|200px|Assembly constituencies in Clwyd 2007]]\n|-\n| 2. [[Alyn and Deeside (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Alyn and Deeside CC (Assembly)]]\n|-\n| 3. [[Clwyd South (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Clwyd South CC (Assembly)]]\n|-\n| 4. [[Clwyd West (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Clwyd West CC (Assembly)]]\n|-\n| 5. [[Delyn (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Delyn CC (Assembly)]]\n|-\n| 6. [[Vale of Clwyd (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Vale of Clwyd CC (Assembly)]]\n|-\n| 7. [[Wrexham (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Wrexham CC (Assembly)]]\n|}\n\nThe seven constituencies are all in the [[North Wales (National Assembly for Wales electoral region)|North Wales]] electoral region, which also includes two [[List of Parliamentary constituencies in Gwynedd|Gwynedd constituencies]].\n\n=== 1999 to 2007 ===\n\n{| border=1 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" \n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Assembly region !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency boundaries\n|-\n| 1. [[Alyn and Deeside (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Alyn and Deeside CC (Assembly)]] || rowspan=5| [[North Wales (National Assembly for Wales electoral region)|North Wales]] || rowspan=8| [[Image:ClwydParliamentaryConstituenciesPre2007.png|left|Assembly constituencies in Clwyd pre-2007]]\n|-\n| 2. [[Clwyd South (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Clwyd South CC (Assembly)]] (part)\n|-\n| 3. [[Clwyd West (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Clwyd West CC (Assembly)]]\n|-\n| 4. [[Conwy (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Conwy CC (Assembly)]] (part)\n|-\n| 5. [[Delyn (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Delyn CC (Assembly)]]\n|-\n| 6. [[Meirionnydd Nant Conwy (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Meirionnydd Nant Conwy CC (Assembly)]] (part) || [[Mid and West Wales (National Assembly for Wales electoral region)|Mid and West Wales]]\n|-\n| 7. [[Vale of Clwyd (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Vale of Clwyd CC (Assembly)]] || rowspan=2| [[North Wales (National Assembly for Wales electoral region)|North Wales]]\n|- \n| 8. [[Wrexham (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Wrexham CC (Assembly)]]\n|}\n\n==Results==\n\n===Westminster elections===\n\n{|\n|-\n! 2005\n! 2010\n! 2015\n! 2017\n|-\n| [[File:UK general election 2005 (Clwyd).png|200px|Results of the UK general election 2005 for Clwyd]]\n| [[File:UK general election 2010 (Clwyd).png|200px|Results of the UK general election 2010 for Clwyd]]\n| [[File:UK general election 2015 (Clwyd).png|200px|Results of the UK general election 2015 for Clwyd]]\n| [[File:UK general election 2010 (Clwyd).png|200px|Results of the UK general election 2010 for Clwyd]]\n|}\n\n===Assembly elections===\n\n{|\n|-\n! 2007\n! 2011\n! 2016\n|-\n| [[File:National Assembly for Wales election 2007 (